liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Woolworths says the improved profit results represent robust sales growth, a more stable operating environment after the cost of COVID in 2022, and more business investment. Food sales increased by 5 per cent over the year to $48 billion as prices rose because of inflation. Gross margins increased but the supermarket chain says it saw higher rates of theft which contributed to stock loss. It has rolled out Scan Assist technology across 474 supermarkets to improve the accuracy of scanning. Increased investment in its Everyday Rewards scheme also offset higher margins. Overall sales rose by 5.7 per cent to $64.3 billion. Woolworths says cost increases in commodities, energy and labour led to above-trend price increases from suppliers during the year, especially in packaged products and dairy. Floods also affected fruit and vegetable prices, although availability and prices improved over the second half of the year. Department store Big W saw a bigger slowdown in spending particarly over the last months of the 2023 financial year. "Increasingly customers are buying only what they need, which has seen a decline in items purchased compared to the prior year."
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Food sales boost Woolworths bottom line

children.content: Woolworths says the improved profit results represent robust sales growth, a more stable operating environment after the cost of COVID in 2022, and more business investment.
Food sales increased by 5 per cent over the year to $48 billion as prices rose because of inflation.
Gross margins increased but the supermarket chain says it saw higher rates of theft which contributed to stock loss.
It has rolled out Scan Assist technology across 474 supermarkets to improve the accuracy of scanning.
Increased investment in its Everyday Rewards scheme also offset higher margins.
Overall sales rose by 5.7 per cent to $64.3 billion.
Woolworths says cost increases in commodities, energy and labour led to above-trend price increases from suppliers during the year, especially in packaged products and dairy.
Floods also affected fruit and vegetable prices, although availability and prices improved over the second half of the year.
Department store Big W saw a bigger slowdown in spending particarly over the last months of the 2023 financial year.
"Increasingly customers are buying only what they need, which has seen a decline in items purchased compared to the prior year."

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Supermarket giant Woolworths has seen annual profit rise slightly for the year for continuing operations. Revenue rose by nearly 6 per cent with after tax profit up nearly 5 per cent to $1.62 billion. Bottom line for 2023: Net profit: -79.6 per cent to $1.62 billion Profit from continuing operations: +4.6 per cent to $1.62 billion Revenue: +5.7 per cent to $64.3 billion Final dividend: 58 cents a share fully franked +9.4 per cent Woolworths says a key challenges over the year were rising cost of living pressures, global supply chain disruptions, severe weather events and regulatory reform.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Woolworths profit increases

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Sam Burgess' time at South Sydney appears to be at an end after the Rabbitohs assistant coach left training early on Wednesday morning. Burgess indicated he would make a statement in due course after leaving the club's training centre this morning but said: "I wish the boys all the well (sic)." Club chairman Nick Pappas left soon after Burgess and said: "We wish Sam all the best." Burgess — a club legend who holds a close bond with club co-owner Russell Crowe — has clashed with head coach Jason Demetriou. Burgess is set to join Super League club Warrington next year. Reporting by AAP
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Burgess out of the Rabbitohs as first casualty of Souths coaching cull

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese's office has confirmed he'll announce the date for the Voice to Parliament referendum at an event in Adelaide on Wednesday next week. The Prime Minister has previously said the vote will happen in October or November. Australians will vote either 'yes' or 'no' on whether a Voice – which would act as an independent advisory body for First Nations people – should be enshrined in the constitution. It is widly tipped the date will be October 14 however the actual date of the referendum has not been confirmed.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Date for Voice to Parliament to be announced
